					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hornby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1259135); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1259135&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182714" alt="Hornby" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1259135)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hornby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1259135); return false;" >Hornby</a></span> <span class="odate time_1340339886 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 Jun 2012 04:38</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1486796">
									

<p>&quot;Debunk&quot; is such a strong word&#8230; this is just an alternate interpretation. One of the things I liked about writing SCP-1050 is there's a lot we know about it, but there's also a helluva lot we <em>don't</em> know and can only guess about. And there's no clear way for the Foundation to fill in the gaps in its knowledge (which, when you think about it, would probably terrify it as much as or more as whatever the threat turned out to be).</p>
<p>Rex could be right, and all the conjectures in the SCP-1050 article could be absolutely wrong.</p>
<p>Or all the conjectures in the SCP-1050 could be absolutely right, and Rex could be wrong.</p>
<p>It's up to you and your headcanon to decide. We won't know for certain until <strong>[DATA EXPUNGED BY O5 COMMAND]</strong> when the 'Destroyers' either do, or do not, show up.</p>

							</div>

								
